messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path:
- /api/users/{id}

All methods acceptable:
- false

Allowed methods (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the user router at the prefix "/api/users" (app.use('/api/users', userRoutes);).
- routes/userRoutes.js defines a route for "/:id" and attaches handlers for .delete(..., deleteUser), .get(..., getUserById) and .put(..., updateUser). Combining the mount prefix and the route path yields the full path "/api/users/{id}".
- The controllers (controllers/userController.js) include implementations and comments confirming the HTTP methods: getUserById is used for GET /api/users/:id, updateUser for PUT /api/users/:id, and deleteUser for DELETE /api/users/:id.
- There is no router or app-level .all, .options, .head, .trace, .post, or .patch registration for this path in the provided code. Per your instruction to base acceptance only on the code (not on framework default behavior), HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, POST, and PATCH are marked false.
- Note: the route handlers are protected by middleware (protect, admin) in routes/userRoutes.js, so these methods require the corresponding authentication/authorization as implemented, but that does not change which HTTP methods are registered.
